We first extract the data from the provided statements:

1. Debt to Asset Ratio  
 • From the balance sheet (“End_date”: 2024-02-01):  
  – Total Assets = 12,566,098.56  
  – Total Liabilities: The only liabilities given are Current Liabilities = 1,601,835.08  
 • Therefore, Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 1,601,835.08 / 12,566,098.56 ≈ 0.1274  
  Rounded to two decimals, this is ≈ 0.13.

2. Gross Profit Margin  
 • From the income statement (2024-02-01):  
  – Gross Profit = 1,136,701.10  
  – Total Revenue = 6,836,701.10  
 • Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (1,136,701.10 / 6,836,701.10) × 100% ≈ 16.63%

3. Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
 • From the cash flow statement (2024-02-01):  
  – Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -6,856,840.58  
 • From the balance sheet, we already have the Total Current Liabilities = 1,601,835.08  
 • Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities  
  = -6,856,840.58 / 1,601,835.08 ≈ -4.278  
  Rounded to two decimals, this is ≈ -4.28.

Thus, the solution in the required format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.13",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "16.63%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-4.28"
  }
}
